author: The Record
title: H.S. boys soccer: Bergen Catholic top seed for county tournament - Boys Soccer
text:
Bergen Catholic (6-0-2) earned the top seed at the Bergen County tournament boys soccer seeding meeting held Sunday in Wyckoff.
Taking the No. 2 seed was Bergen Tech (6-0), followed by Tenafly (6-0-1) and Ramapo (6-1). Only the top four of 20 schools earned byes.
Play-in games will match Park Ridge at Wallington, North Arlington at Mahwah, Lyndhurst at Cliffside Park and Emerson at Ridgewood at 4 p.m., Thursday, unless the teams mutually agree to play later. The second round is Sunday with four games at Ramapo High School and four at Emerson.
The quarters are Oct. 18 at Ramsey, the semis are Oct. 24 at Indian Hills, and the final is 7 p.m., Oct. 30 at Ramapo.
Ramapo won last year, defeating Northern Highlands, 2-1, and the Green Raiders have won two of the past three tournaments.
Bergen Catholic last won in 1999, defeating Don Bosco, 1-0, in the title game of the tournament that began in 1972. Teams had to have at least a .500 record to be considered and a .650 winning percentage or higher meant automatic qualification.
